political sensitivities behind aircraft purchasing.
Air France was puzzled by Mr Baudis' objections as the group has been buying
Boeings, alongside Airbuses, for years. The latest order simply replaces a
cancelled order for two Boeing 747-400s.
French industrial output in the third quarter of 1991 rose 0.9 per cent over
the previous three months, Insee, the state statistics body, said, Alice
Rawsthorn writes from Paris.
