FT  05 FEB 92 / International Capital Markets: Australian corporate bond
issues climb to ADollars 7.19bn
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TOTAL issuance in the Australian corporate bond market rose 9.5 per cent to
ADollars 7.19bn last year, according to investment bank Bain and Co, Reuter
reports.
Bain said this pushed total outstanding issues in the market to ADollars
18.8bn at December 31, reflecting an impressive growth rate since the
market's inception in 1988. It said notable features of 1991 included the
relaxation of controls on borrowings by foreign governments and
international organisations.
'The creation of a new category of supranational foreign borrowers is an
exciting development for the domestic market,' Bain said in its annual
corporate bond market review.
Foreign organisations to tap the Australian markets in 1991 were the
European Investment Bank which issued ADollars 400m of bonds and Eurofima
which issued ADollars 200m. Corporate bond issuance rose to ADollars 6.5bn
in 1990 from ADollars 2.65bn in 1989 and ADollars 3.58bn in 1988. Bain said
AAA-rated issuers accounted for 69.5 per cent of 1991 issues - 94.1 per cent
in the first half of 1991. It said this reflected investors' preoccupation
with credit worthiness.
