<HEADLINE>
FT  05 FEB 92 / UK investor will return to face charges
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Foreign Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Terry Ramsden, the former City investor known for his lavish lifestyle,
yesterday waived extradition in a Los Angeles federal court and agreed to
return to the UK to face fraud charges in connection with dealings in
Japanese equity warrants through his investment company Glen International.
His lawyer declined to say what prompted Mr Ramsden's decision, but said his
waiver included an agreement with the Serious Fraud Office to recommend bail
of 'a reasonable amount' based on a financial statement Mr Ramsden will
submit on arrival in the UK.
Charges he faces in the UK include fraudulent trading, obtaining property by
deception, evading debts by deception and making false statements to
investigators.
Last month a federal judge denied bail to Mr Ramsden, who has been in
custody since his arrest on September 8 in Beverly Hills, Los Angeles.
</TEXT>
