Lufthansa had also experienced a final quarter worse than hoped because of
the continued weak state of the world economy. Full results will be
announced in May.
The airline, just over half of whose equity is state-owned, began the year
poorly with a loss of DM475m in the first quarter, a period which suffered
from the impact on business of the Gulf war. But it made a profit of DM145m
in the second quarter and DM172m in the third.
Lufthansa's 1991 loss comes despite higher traffic volumes and turnover.
