3 per cent in the year.
The company, like others in its sector, warned that the highly competitive
conditions seen last year were spilling into 1992.
Kroger, which operates over 1,250 stores in 25 states and geared itself up
in a defensive restructuring in 1988, opened or expanded 42 stores last
year.
