FT  05 FEB 92 / Observer: Blocking copy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It was good to see, on a visit to a packed-out north London computer
auction, that competitive juices still run strongly even in the newest of
business niches. Inside, over 400 people were bidding Pounds 10 or so for
recycled software and anything up to Pounds 1,200 for nearly new
high-powered PCs.
Outside, rival south London auctioneers were leafleting the hundreds of
parked cars with advertising copy. Alas for their efforts, the north
London team were following them round, removing the ads from each and every
car.
Technology's all very well, but when it comes to commercial success, you
can't beat plain old aggression.
