FT  05 FEB 92 / Gangs in boat people camps clash for second night
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Riot police leave Hong Kong's Shek Kong camp for Vietnamese boat people
yesterday. Gangs among the camp inmates clashed for a second night after at
least 21 people had burned to death on Monday in the worst violence to
strike the colony's boat people camps.
