FT  05 FEB 92 / Marchand refuses to quit over Habash
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ASSOCIATED PRESS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FRENCH interior minister Philippe Marchand refused to resign yesterday over
the harsh criticism of Palestinian leader Mr George Habash's visit to
France, Associated Press reports from Paris.
Meanwhile, a voter poll, published in the newspaper Le Parisien, found 55
per cent in favour of bringing forward the National Assembly elections which
are scheduled for spring next year; 39 per cent were opposed.
The poll reflected surging discontent with the governing Socialist Party
over a stagnant economy, long-running finance scandals and what is now known
as 'the Habash affair.'
President Francois Mitterrand was scheduled to give a television interview
on the controversy last night.
