FT  04 FEB 92 / UK Company News: GPG to send report and accounts late
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GPG, the investment company run by Sir Ron Brierley, the New Zealand
entrepreneur, will be sending its 1991 report and accounts to its UK and New
Zealand shareholders three weeks later than the New Zealand Stock Exchange
had stipulated.
NZSE regulations required completion by January 31 and the London Stock
Exchange by March 31. The company had intended to meet the earlier date but
the preparation of the accounts on the basis of the new UK Financial
Reporting Exposure Draft 1, as yet unadopted by the UK Accounting Standards
Review Board, has taken longer than expected.
The NZSE was informed of the likely delay on January 22 and a waiver was
sought. It was denied.
