FT  04 FEB 92 / Observer: Factinating
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fans of useless trivia will be delighted by a new booklet produced by Boots
entitled Some Fascinating Facts.
Did you know, for example, that an elephant weighs as much as the frames of
339,286 pairs of sunglasses? Or that right-handed people use more deodorants
than the left-handed because they sweat more? Or that it takes 15 inflated
condoms to float a jeep?
I thought not.
