FT  04 FEB 92 / Parliament and Politics: Ashdown strengthens election stance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Paddy Ashdown (above) yesterday further hardened his party's negotiating
stance if the Liberal Democrats hold the balance of power in a hung
parliament after the election.
He said his party was prepared to force another election almost immediately
if his terms for a coalition were not met.
Speaking on BBC's Panorama programme, Mr Ashdown said he was prepared to see
that the 'government is removed if they have ignored the view of the
electorate.' He has stressed that a commitment to electoral reform for the
House of Commons and an agreed legislative programme for a full parliament
would be preconditions of Liberal Democrat support.
